$ document.compatMode

The value of the property `document.compatMode` is dependent on the → development/web/browser/layout-engine#browser-rendering-mode[rendering mode] of a → development/web/browser/layout-engine[web browser's layout engine]. It is set to one of the following two values:
    • `BackCompat` (quirks mode)
    • `CSS1Compat` (no-quicks mode)

The following document reports `compatMode` to be `CSS1Compat`:
gh|Browser-Object-Model|/document/compatMode/no-quirks.html||

This document reports `compatMode` to be `BackCompat`:
gh|Browser-Object-Model|/document/compatMode/quirks.html||

sa:
  The `→ development/web/browser/object-model/document` object
